The paper deals with physical-layer techniques for multi-antenna broadcast channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The focus on maximizing spectral and energy efficiency is also relevant to networking and communications (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of precoders and message splitting is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and the optimization algorithms used are related to computer networking and communications (cs.COM).
